This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with image recognition and classification. It also involves the use of semantic information, which is a common technique in computer vision. The paper also proposes an end-to-end framework, which suggests that it may fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category. Additionally, the use of soft label embedding loss indicates that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques, such as semantic relationships among classes, which suggests that it may fall under the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) category. Finally, the use of visual attribute datasets suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) category.
